        "timestamp": 1742382938
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am not aware of any reference for comprehension categories.</p>\n<p>In the case of categories with families, the contextual slice can be defined as the contextual core of the slice CwF: </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathcal{C} // \\Gamma = \\mathsf{cxl}(\\mathcal{C} / \\Gamma) </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord\">//Γ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">cxl</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord\">/Γ</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>The contextual core <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathsf{cxl}(\\mathcal{C}) </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">cxl</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> of a CwF <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathcal{C} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span> has the following universal property: <br>\n  for every map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">D</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F : \\mathcal{D} \\to \\mathcal{C} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span>  with  bijective actions on types and terms, the inclusion map  <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathsf{cxl}(\\mathcal{C}) \\to \\mathcal{C} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">cxl</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span> factors uniquely through <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> F </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span>. This can also be phrased using an orthogonal factorization system.<br>\n(AFAIK, the earliest reference for this is this note of Christian Sattler: <a href=\"https://www.cse.chalmers.se/~sattler/docs/normalization-by-evaluation.pdf\">https://www.cse.chalmers.se/~sattler/docs/normalization-by-evaluation.pdf</a>)</p>\n<p>Moreover, if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathcal{C} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span> itself is contextual, we have <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> (\\mathcal{C} // \\Gamma) \\cong (\\mathcal{C}[\\underline{\\gamma} : 1 \\to \\Gamma]) </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord\">//Γ</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1444em;vertical-align:-0.3944em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6456em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05556em;\">γ</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3944em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Γ</span><span class=\"mclose\">])</span></span></span></span>, where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> (\\mathcal{C}[\\underline{\\gamma} : 1 \\to \\Gamma]) </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1444em;vertical-align:-0.3944em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6456em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05556em;\">γ</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3944em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Γ</span><span class=\"mclose\">])</span></span></span></span> is the free extension of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathcal{C} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span> by a new morphism from the terminal object to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\Gamma </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Γ</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>I would imagine that analogous universal properties can be proven for comprehension categories. The situation is a bit more complicated because comprehension categories form a 2-category while CwFs form a 1-category.</p>",
